# Purpose: Keep generated files, secrets, and local Python tooling out of git.
# Input/Output: Git reads this file while deciding what to track.
# Invariants: Real secrets must never be committed; example files stay versioned.
# Debugging: If a file is unexpectedly ignored, run `git check-ignore -v <path>`.

.DS_Store
.env
.env.local
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
coverage.xml
htmlcov/
.venv/
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/
secrets/*
!secrets/.gitkeep

